<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-22T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-22T23:00:00-05:00" n="445" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13821: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-23T12:00:00+08:00">December 23,
                                1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 23—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>633. Nanking’s 372, December 22, midnight [<hi rend="italic">noon?</hi>].
                            A representative of the Military Attaché’s office, probably Colonel
                            Stilwell himself, will leave for Loyang tonight. I told Colonel Stilwell
                            that he should strongly urge evacuation of American citizens from Shensi
                            if evacuation is possible.</p>
                        <p>Nanking and Shanghai informed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>